### HYMN CXXXVII

#### A charm to promote the growth of hair

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0613701">1</span></span>The Plant
which Jamadagni dug to make his daughter's locks.  
   grow long,  
  This same hath Vitahavya brought to us from Asita's abode.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0613702">2</span></span>They might
be measured with a rein, meted with both extended  
   arms.  
  Let the black locks spring thick and strong and grow like reeds  
   upon thy head.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0613703">3</span></span>Strengthen
the roots, prolong the points, lengthen the middle  
   part, O Plant.  
  Let the black locks spring thick and strong and grow like reeds  
   upon thy head.

